parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience electrical malfunctions, which can lead to accidents, inconvenience, and safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies
warning lights illuminate on the dashboard
the radio and other electrical components malfunction
the doors unlock and the seatbelt moves back and forth
smoke fills the interior
and sparks are visible under the dash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the distributor system can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, and experience poor idling, which can lead to accidents, inconvenience, and safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies
the engine jerks or hesitates
the distributor housing makes a noise and is worn out
the car stops idling
and the ignition coil
distributor cap
and rotor fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause the vehicle to blow warm air, which can lead to discomfort and inconvenience.
symptoms: The air conditioning blows warm air
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle requires frequent repairs to the air conditioning system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to remain unretracted, making it difficult or impossible to wear the seat belt properly, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt remains unretracted
the seat belt warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
the seat belt is unable to remain fastened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can lead to loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distance, and accidents, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: ABS system failure
total loss of braking
indicator light comes on
brakes function inadequately
require excessive pressure
extended stopping distance
shimmy or vibration when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to increased risk of injury or fatalities in the event of a collision.
symptoms: No deployment of airbags during vehicle collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine catching fire can cause serious damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine fire while driving
especially in construction areas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or die while driving, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Car dies while slowing down in traffic
battery working but ignition not turning over
steering wheel and transmission locked up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive vibration and overheating can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potential breakdowns.
symptoms: Noticeable vibration in the engine when idling
tremendous vibration when in reverse and when the A/C is on
vibration when downshifting to second gear
overheating problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine timing belt can cause serious engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potential breakdowns.
symptoms: Engine timing belt failure.
